title.narrative: 6.2 THE NATIONAL SYSTEM IS STRENGTHENEDFOR VULNERABLE CHILDREN TO ACCESS

description.narrative: The national system is strengthened for vulnerable children to access integrated and inclusive social protection services., which contributes to Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Early Childhood Development, Evaluation And Research, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Skills Development, Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved policy environment and systems for disadvantaged and excluded children, guided by data and knowledge.

title.narrative: The national system is strengthened for vulnerable children to access integrated and inclusive social protection services.

description.narrative: Technical assistance provided to NAF contributed to inclusion of 230,000 daily worker in the social protection emergency cash assistance scheme, and around 1,000,000 households in the bread subsidy scheme during the past 4 months, while the UNICEF cash assistance program programs continued its monthly education-labeled cash transfers to cover 11,404 children in vulnerable communities. Additionally, over 128,000 children and parents have been covered by at least one Makani service including 9,000 beneficiaries from marginalized communities. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/08/2020
